  "description": "Musaceae is a family of monocots comprising Musa (60+ species — all bananas and plantains) and Ensete (7 species — Ethiopian banana/false banana). The cultivated banana Musa × paradisiaca and dessert banana varieties derived from M. acuminata are among the world's most important food crops. Called Kela in Hindi, Vaazha in Tamil, Arati in Telugu. India is one of the world's largest banana producers.",
